{\rtf1\ansi \deff0{\fonttbl{\f8\fswiss Arial;}}\margl720\margr2160\pgnstart218\sectd\pgnrestart\pgnstarts218\footery1080{\header \pard\plain\ql MYARC ADVANCED BASIC\par }{\footer \pard\plain\ql \chpgn     VERSION 4.0  DDI SOFTWARE  \par }\pard \plain\f8\fs20 TIME/TIME$\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab      TIME/TIME$\par \par \par \par \par Description\par The computer has an internal clock that can be accessed from BASIC.\par \par TIME$ can be used to read the clock and TIME to set the clock.\par \par TO SET CLOCK\par \par Format\par CALL TIME("hh:mm:ss")\par \par The string length is always 8 characters. Therefore an hour less than 10 must be preceded by a 0.\par \par The clock works on 24 hour time so all times after 12 noon must have 12 hours added to them.\par \par Example\par \par CALL TIME("06:15:00")\tab \tab 6:15 A. M.\par CALL TIME("18:15:00")\tab \tab 6:15 P. M.\par \par TO READ CLOCK\par \par Format\par PRINT TIME$\par OR\par T$=TIME$\par \par Example\par \par 10 CALL CLEAR\par 20 DISPLAY AT(24,1):TIME$\par 30 GOTO 20\par \par 10 CALL TIME("00:00:00")\par 20 FOR I=1 TO 10000\par 30 NEXT I\par 40 PRINT TIME$\par \par This is an easy to see how long a program takes to execute.\par }
